&lt;p>&lt;strong>Solution Consultant&lt;/strong>&lt;br/>&lt;strong>Clearance requirement: Must have a Secret clearance&lt;/strong>&lt;br/>&lt;strong>Location:&amp;nbsp; Remote US&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Juniper Networks provides strategic solution development, integration, and deployment services to our customers through the Professional Services organization. The Solution Consultant will work remotely, providing primarily post-sales delivery, and will deliver and own the success of all technical aspects of the customer deliverables. This role will have the technical and project experience to interface directly with sales and the customer to define the problem from the customer’s perspective and will have the ability to design/validate complex network and/or automation solutions involving multiple technical disciplines.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Requirements:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Remote: US-based&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Security Clearance Required: Secret&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Highly technical role providing post-sales Engineering Design/Architecture, Operational, and Support of Juniper products within a customer infrastructure.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The ideal candidate will have 5+ years of Network Engineering Design/Architecture, Operational, and Support experience in Service Provider, Enterprise, and Data Center network environments.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The candidate must have a detailed understanding of protocols used for IP networks and demonstratable technical expertise in the configuration, troubleshooting and operation of IP-based routers, switches, and security devices.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The candidate will be flexible and comfortable working in multiple verticals: WAN/LAN Networking, MIST (wireless &amp; wire), Data Center and automation.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Support: MX, EX, QFX and SRX&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Solutions: MIST Wireline/Wireless, Apstra, Paragon, and other automation solutions.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Travel: ~10% to 20% (based on project requirements)&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Qualifications:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Solid understanding of routing and switching protocols associated with IP networks: OSPF, IS-IS, ISIS-SR, BGP, MPLS, L3VPN,&amp;nbsp;EVPN-VXLAN, multicast, associated tunneling technologies (GRE, IPsec, etc.), Class of Service (CoS), Filter-Based Forwarding (policy based static routing).&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Understanding of network security.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience with Automation Frameworks, Linux, Virtualization, and Programming Languages.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Preferred Automation/orchestration skills: Python and Ansible (leveraging PyEZ), CI/CD workflows &amp; NetDevOps, docker, Netbox, GitLab.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>SD-WAN: 128T/SSR is a plus.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Data Center Design and deployments leveraging Apstra or other Data Center orchestration platforms.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>MIST Wireless and/or wired is a plus.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Paragon suite automation is a plus.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Certifications such as JNCIS, JNCIP, JNCIE, CCNP, and CCIE.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Ideal Strengths&lt;/strong>:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Strong interpersonal, communication, and presentation skills.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Ability to effectively work independently and function in a team environment.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Demonstrated ability to manage multiple projects and work calmly under pressure.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Ability to prioritize work activities to achieve customer goals and deliverables.&lt;/li>
