&lt;div style="border-width:0px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;">
 &lt;strong>Job Description&lt;/strong>
&lt;/div>
&lt;div style="border-width:0px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;">
 &amp;nbsp;
&lt;/div>
&lt;div style="border-width:0px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;">
 &lt;strong>Position: SDN Cloud Consultant /Architect&lt;/strong>&lt;br/>&lt;strong>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>
&lt;/div>
&lt;div style="font-style:normal;font-weight:400;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;">
 &lt;div style="border-width:0px;font-style:inherit;font-weight:inherit;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
  &lt;div style="border-width:0px;font-style:inherit;font-weight:inherit;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
   &lt;div style="border-width:0px;font-style:inherit;font-weight:inherit;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
    &lt;div style="border-width:0px;font-style:inherit;font-weight:inherit;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
     &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
      &lt;p>This is a highly technical role, providing primarily offshore post-sales Consulting delivery under the Juniper Networks Professional Services Team. The role covers Architectural, Design and Implementation Consultancy services for Junipers Networks Solutions. Consultant will be required to develop and maintain expertise on&amp;nbsp;SDN&amp;nbsp;Architectures and solutions.&lt;/p>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       &amp;nbsp;
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       There is a wide range of technical offerings which the Consultant will be expected to deliver, ranging from Design, Deployment, Configuration, Customization and Training. The role involves taking the Juniper products, and ensuring the effective delivery of the products, and configuring or customizing it to meet the customer’s requirements. This also includes being able to clearly outline the products capabilities, consult with the customer to understand and document their requirements, shape, define and agree designs, implement the solution, and configuring the products into the customer environment, using technical and personal skills to achieve this objective.
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       &amp;nbsp;
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       &amp;nbsp;
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       &lt;strong>Typical activities are around the following key areas:&lt;/strong>
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       &amp;nbsp;
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Facilitating workshops to identify and understand customer requirements
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Providing guidance on Network Architectures
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Developing and documenting High-Level and Low-Level Network Designs
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Design Validation and Verification testing
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Interoperability testing
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Network Implementation planning
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Troubleshooting/fault finding
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Knowledge Transfer activities
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       &amp;nbsp;
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       &amp;nbsp;
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       The main purpose of this job is to work with Juniper Networks customers to ensure the smooth design, planning, migration, and integration of Juniper Networks Products into new and/or existing network.
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       &amp;nbsp;
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       The Consultant is expected to provide guidance and is (technically) leading in order to provide high quality network design, service design, planning, engineering and implementation consulting services to the customer, to maintain high levels of customer satisfaction and thereby increase potential business opportunities.
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       &amp;nbsp;
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       &lt;strong>&amp;nbsp;Primary skills and experience required:&lt;/strong>
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       &amp;nbsp;
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Expert communication and interpersonal skills, this means you like talking to people...yes in person, too!
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       The mature “customer first” focus so that you personally can close out operational challenges on both sales and delivery with CSS, Sales, Partners, or other Juniper players
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Strong design and implementation experience
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Commitment to delivering a remarkable customer experience
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Bachelor of Science in Engineering/Comp Science or similar discipline
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Excellent and deep hands on and planning capabilities in TCP/IP, MPLS, Traffic Engineering, IGP, BGP, Internet peering/exchanges
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Very strong knowledge of the design principles and operations in SP networks.
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Extensive experience in a technical role including strong experience supporting large SP networks and mobile backhaul solutions
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
       Excellent Customer handling and communication (verbal and written) skills
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div style="border-width:0px;margin:0px;padding:0px;">
