&lt;p>Juniper Networks has an immediate opening for a team-oriented, highly effective, and motivated technical leader Senior Sales Engineering Manager (SSEM). This position reports to the Director of Sales Engineering. This SSEM position will provide consistent team and business leadership with a focus on Service Provider sales growth, technical and operational excellence, and SE development for Juniper’s Canadian Service Providers.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The position is responsible for tactical and strategic leadership to the Canadian Service Providers Sales Engineering team. Accountabilities focus on outcome-based technical enablement through sales engagement, team development, and alignment of organizational capability to create a positive bias for Juniper products, solutions, and services. The area of focus also includes the definition and adaptation of SP transformation initiatives as the market continues to evolve toward cloud and software-oriented networking. The SSEM will team with the Regional Sales leader(s) and develop key relationships and ownership along with Juniper Corporate, field SE and sales management leading to a more integrated go-to-market model (GTM).&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The successful candidate will be an accomplished self-starter with leadership experience; aware of market trends and transitions; understand data network systems architecture and associated business value; have experience or familiarity with channel and system integrator business motions; have proven track record to work in a matrix environment and possess excellent communication, presentation, and organization skills.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Balanced professional, technical and intuition for business is fundamental.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Regional and Corporate travel (20% and variable)&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Primary Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Sales strategy and execution plan to accelerate and achieve revenue targets&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Increase SP awareness, preference, and purchase of Juniper products, solutions, and services with metrics on effectiveness.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Structured technical enablement initiatives including technical reviews, Proofs of Concept (POCs) demonstrations, events, webinars, and workshops&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Alignment of SE resources to business plans and channel imperatives&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Set team/individual goals and objectives in support of SP strategy&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>SE staffing, development and workflow&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Business operations and administrative functions&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Serve as a technical executive for Canadian SPs&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Model the ‘Juniper Way’ and company values&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>Qualifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>5+ years proven experience in technology sales leadership roles with a strong background in LAN/WAN infrastructure; architecture; concepts and associated technologies&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Thorough understanding of the pre-sales engineering and sales processes ideally with experience in channel and systems integrator models&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Familiarity with current networking and business model trends, market dynamics and technological adjacencies (i.e. virtualization, SW subscription models, cloud services)&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Ability to assess, prioritize, assign and manage technical workstreams to completion&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Demonstrated strong written, oral and presentation skills with the ability to discuss highly technical concepts to a variety of audiences, including executive-level technical decision-makers&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Strong interpersonal, organizational and collaborative work skills&lt;/li>
