&lt;p>&lt;strong>&lt;u>About the Position:&lt;/u>&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Are you passionate about innovating and building products and solutions that power the scalable, feature-rich networks of a connected, AI-enabled world? Do you want to see yourself being part of, and leading the build-out of network infrastructure that is at the foundation of such technology revolution?&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Come and be part of the Packet Forwarding Engine (PFE) for Cloud Ready Data Centre (CRDC), which is helping realize Juniper’s vision of such next generation Data Centre products and solutions.&amp;nbsp;You should join the team, if:&lt;br/>- You love learning and problem-solving&lt;br/>- You love to work amongst a highly driven and talented team of engineers, with a long track record of excellence&lt;br/>- You take pride in writing quality software, building products, and above all, solving some of the most demanding networking problems&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>&lt;u>Responsibilities:&lt;/u>&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
 &lt;li>Articulate design, lead development and see through the deployment of switching software for Juniper enterprise and datacenter switching products.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work with Product management and other cross functional teams and develop detailed architectural, functional and design specifications to meet product requirements.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Carry out detailed design, coding, unit and functional testing of software, fix complex defects, through entire lifecycle of the project.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Lead development activity within the team, working with managers for detailed planning of tasks, setting intermediate milestones, strategizing execution.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Mentor and guide junior engineers in the team for technical problem solving, and building long term expertise and competency.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work with cross functional validation/verification teams&amp;nbsp;to ensure correct and complete verification of software and components, to meet real-life network&amp;nbsp;deployments.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work closely with Juniper Technical Assistance Team, for providing engineering assistance in supporting critical customer escalations.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>&lt;u>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u>&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>&lt;u>Requirements:&lt;/u>&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
 &lt;li>Bachelor’s or master’s degree in computer science or similar discipline, with 15+ years of experience in networking and system software development&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Expert in data networking with in-depth knowledge in routing, switching, Layer-2 and Layer-3 forwarding, QOS, overlay technologies, e.g., EVPN, VXLAN, tunneling features, e.g., MPLS, GRE etc.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Knowledgeable in high-speed packet forwarding technologies, e.g., network processors, and newer programmable forwarding models e.g., P4 or equivalent.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Thorough understanding of Layer2, Layer3 protocols, e.g., Spanning Tree Protocol (STP), LACP, OSPF, BGP, ISIS, BFD.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Must have superlative problem-solving skills, proficiency in coding in C/C++ and debugging skills, must be expert in data structures and algorithms.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Must have thorough systems knowledge in fundamental OS concepts in Linux or similar OS, skills to debug hard system level issues.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Expertise in scripting technologies and techniques, familiarity with state-of-the-art devops methodologies and practices&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Good articulation and presentation skills on technical topics and subjects&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol></DESCRLONG></JN_CAREERS_SITE_DETAILS><JN_CAREERS_SITE_DETAILS><HRS_JOB_OPENING_ID>1009508</HRS_JOB_OPENING_ID><POSTING_TITLE>Software Engineer Staff</POSTING_TITLE><CITY>Bengaluru</CITY><STATE>KA</STATE><COUNTRY>IND</COUNTRY><LOCATION_DESCR>Bengaluru, IND Elnath-Exora</LOCATION_DESCR><JOB_POSTING_DT>11/20/2023</JOB_POSTING_DT><URL>https://careers.juniper.net/#/jobdescription?jid=1009508</URL><URL_1>https://ejif.fa.us6.oraclecloud.com:443/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX/job/1009508</URL_1><STATE_DESCR> </STATE_DESCR><COUNTRY_DESCR>India</COUNTRY_DESCR><JOB_CATEGORY_CODE>SW</JOB_CATEGORY_CODE><JOB_CATEGORY_DESCR>Software Engineering</JOB_CATEGORY_DESCR><RECRUITING_TYPE_CODE>Experienced</RECRUITING_TYPE_CODE><DESCRLONG>
