&lt;p>&lt;strong>Strategic Enterprise Account Manager – French speaker based in Switzerland&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>About Juniper&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>At Juniper, we strive to deliver network experiences that transform how people connect, work and live.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>By challenging the inherent complexity in the Cloud + 5G + AI era, our solutions power the connections that matter most - from education to healthcare to secure banking. Our commitment is to advance real outcomes for network teams and every individual they serve.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It’s that simple!&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Why Juniper&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Our vision is for Juniper Networks to become a multi-generational community that empowers people to accomplish the impossible. This requires a perspective that is multi-generational itself, thinking beyond the markets and products of today and tomorrow to the values that enable a community to prosper for generations. We value trust, integrity, respect, humility, being bold and delivering excellence. We're looking for people who live the values of our culture and can bring our vision to life.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>The Role&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>We are looking for a fast starter, innovative, and inspirational Enterprise Account Manager to lead, grow and develop our relationship with a dedicated named customer set across Switzerland`s Romandy. This Account Manager will lead all aspects of the evolution of the account across Romandy and be responsible to identify new business opportunities across all Juniper infrastructure solutions for the Named Accounts, working closely and having existing or building-up new contacts with top executives in the account.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/>With a broad network and a deep understanding of the partner landscape, the Account Manager will&amp;nbsp; liaise and attract new partners to create business value in a Romandy channels.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/>&lt;br/>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The successful candidate will have a proven track record working with Enterprise Accounts and be able to effectively connect with key stakeholders, executing multiple priorities simultaneously.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The role will be exclusively located in Switzerland’s Romandy and will report to our Senior Manager Sales DACH.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>What you will do&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>First person on the ground in Romandy to hunt for and create sustainable business.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Identify and liaise and onboard 3-4 partners to work with Juniper in Switzerland’s Romandy.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Jointly with your management you will identify a set of future key customers in your territory that benefit from Juniper’s value-creating solutions.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Sell Juniper products and solutions to and through partners to your set of Named Accounts that are based in Romandy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Close involvement and interworking with both the client and Juniper touch sales channels, and the wider account team across DACH.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Position end-to-end solutions and articulate Juniper strategies to senior management in the account.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Educate client sales teams about relevant Juniper solutions and selling them the benefits of the Juniper partnership,&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Develop sales strategies for target markets including account targeting, goal setting, messaging, marketing programs etc.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Forecasting, lead and opportunity management and reporting.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Engage with all customer functions involved in or influencing Juniper business developments (Sales, Marketing, Engineering, Services etc.), up to Senior Executive level&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>The persona we are looking for&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Swiss citizen or foreigner with Swiss C-Permit.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Native French and English language (written and spoken) essential.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>German is a huge advantage.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Based in Romandy.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Deep understanding of partner- and customer landscape with existing business relations and a broad network.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Technological enthusiast, knowledge of networking &amp; security solutions, general good overview of new technologies and innovations in the networking industry.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>A proven track record of success (at least the last 5+ years) selling to and through different verticals in Switzerland`s Romandy Enterprise segment.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>10+ years’ experience developing sales strategies, preparing proposals, and presenting networking, security, or related high-tech solutions.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Demonstrable strong communication, presentation, negotiation and closing skills and using a win/win philosophy.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The ability to articulate success record and define how a vendor can make a difference.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Relationship management skills that translate into identifying decision-makers and influencers.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Must have the ability to work autonomously, be self-motivated and a strong team player.&lt;/li>
