&lt;p>&lt;strong>&lt;u>Scrum Master - IT Team&lt;/u>&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Location: anywhere in the U.S.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The Scrum Master is responsible for working across IT teams and business functions to coach IT Delivery teams to a mature Lean Agile framework. Scrum Master ensures their team matures in Agile principles and practices. They make sure the team follows the ceremonies correctly, they remove impediments and keep them focused on what their priorities are on a day-to-day basis.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The Scrum Master works closely with the Business and IT teams to understand and groom requirements for the delivery team. They partner with the IT Project Management Organization (PMO) to ensure timely delivery of project milestones.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>&lt;u>Primary Accountabilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u>&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Coach teams&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;in lean agile methodology; help teams appreciate depths of Lean and Agile practices and principles.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Lead Team&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;translate business requirements into critical data dependencies and requirements.&lt;u>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u>&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Facilitate Agile Ceremonies&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;for Lean Agile teams, including, but not limited to Daily Standup, Story Kickoff &amp; Grooming, Iteration Planning, Iteration Review / Story Showcases&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Responsible for the flow of work&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;delivering completed work to customers, including, Definition of Ready, Definition of Done, Backlog Grooming and Work in Progress (WIP) Limits&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Align Teams&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;with the product vision, sprint goals, and other necessary information.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Partnership&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;within multi-tiered and matrixed organization model to deliver complex requirements.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Champion Continuous Improvement&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;(CI) activities to reduce waste and increase productivity.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Manage impediments&lt;/u>: Communicate to Project Manager and business; clear impediments for delivery teams.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Help the team establish practices&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;that enhance quality, lowers technical debt and increase product value.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Constantly Inform&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;the Project Manager/ Product Owner about impacts to Scope and Time.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Strong Communication Skills&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;Able to Persuade/Influence Others at all Organization Levels and the ability foster lasting partnerships.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Leadership Communication Skills&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;Able to communicate with all levels of leadership across multiple business segments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;u>Do Things Differently&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;by soliciting followership from the functional teams to think beyond the ‘way the things work today'.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
