&lt;p>&lt;strong>Network Engineer - Saudi Arabia&lt;/strong>&lt;br/>&lt;br/>&lt;strong>DESCRIPTION&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Work as an on-site NOC engineer, typically as part of a team, to provide basic expertise in support of the customer's operational requirements.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Works closely with customer and Juniper Technical Assistance Center to resolve issues.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Acts as a first level for Juniper Networks support and development teams.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>KNOWLEDGE&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Maintains a professional knowledge of concepts, practices, and procedures within a particular field.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Has a good experience, product-specific knowledge, and expertise.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Uses professional concepts and company objectives to resolve complex issues in creative and effective ways.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>SUPERVISION&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Receives technical direction from multiple contributors.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Exercises a degree of creativity and latitude.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong>POSITION REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Nationality: Saudi&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Certification: Strong JNCIP-SP or CCIE-SP&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Number of experienced years: 2&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Located on-site with the customer in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work on 24/7 shifts that include Mornings/evenings/Nights.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work with an operation manager/team leader and other professional services consultants providing industry leading technical services to both the customer and partner&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Understand the customer’s organizational structure and become familiar with the network implementation, support processes and procedures.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Troubleshoot equipment and network problems and to track JTAC critical (P1/P2) cases through to problem resolution.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Produce a written summary report of the status of equipment and network problems on a regular basis to the customer.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The ideal candidate for this role should be able to demonstrate most of following skills:&amp;nbsp;
  &lt;ul>
   &lt;li>Good knowledge of Routing Protocols like BGP/ISIS/OSPF, Switching Networks &amp; hands on troubleshooting of networks.&lt;/li>
   &lt;li>Good knowledge of Layer-2 and -3 VPNs and MPLS applications&lt;/li>
   &lt;li>Good knowledge of Juniper Networks M-, MX- and T-series architectures&lt;/li>
   &lt;li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li>
  &lt;/ul>&lt;/li>
