&lt;p>&lt;strong>Commercial Counsel - Netherlands (EMEA Wide)&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Job Description:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>We seek an engaging, organized and self-motivated lawyer to serve as a trusted legal and business advisor to the EMEA Sales team, working in a fast-paced technology business.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You will report to the Associate General Counsel, Senior Director for EMEA Legal.&amp;nbsp; You will be responsible for negotiating commercial transactions and advising on a host of business issues, such as pricing and licensing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You will interact with our customers and partners, as well as a broad spectrum of internal functions, including product groups, sales, services, operations and finance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Required Skills&lt;/strong>:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Law degree from an accredited law school in the EU and practicing certificate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Fluent in English; fluency in other languages is an advantage.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>4-5 years’ experience in handling complex sales transactions, preferably gained from a combination of experience with a large, international technology company and/or a major commercial law firm.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Excellent commercial contracts skills (drafting, negotiating and reviewing) including agreements selling technology solutions, licensing software, selling cloud services, selling complex services plus agreements with our channel partners and marketing agreements.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Able to advise senior management on risk and risk mitigation in a clear, structured manner.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience with revenue recognition and other accounting issues that arise in commercial transactions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Effective verbal and written communication and relationship-building skills.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Able to interact well with senior management, other corporate departments and at all levels of employees.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Handle sensitive situations tactfully yet firmly while maintaining trust and credibility.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Enjoy working and advising in fast-paced situations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Be a business enabler by getting things done and finding solutions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Possess business acumen and understand the company's business.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>To be successful, you will embrace Juniper’s core values establish yourself as a team player who is flexible, creative and intellectually nimble.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>If you have data privacy experience, that is a plus.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Location:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>The position will be hybrid, based at the Juniper offices located in Schipol-Rijk with home-working also enabled.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Travel:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>Business travel across the EU may be required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Relocation is not offered for this position.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>About Juniper&lt;/strong>:&lt;/p>
&lt;p>We strive to deliver a simplified experience for those who run networks and those who depend on them.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>We relentlessly focus on putting our customers – the network architects, builders and operators – at the center of all that we do, so that their customers – the team connecting on Zoom, the associate using a scanner in a store, the student during their online class - are as happy and productive as possible.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It all starts with software innovation.&amp;nbsp; We push the envelope on predictability, programmability, automation, and insights. By making experience the top priority, our customers can build agile networks that transcend customer expectations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
