&lt;p>&lt;strong>&lt;u>Position Overview:&lt;/u>&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Based in or close to Paris, the Sales Manager – has a vital role in driving Juniper’s continued success across the territory and is a key member of the SD’s&amp;nbsp; Management team. The core objective is to grow market share, new customers and drive sales/revenue of Juniper’s products, services and solutions for the region and customers through high touch, channel enabled market coverage models. The Sales Manager will represent, communicate and execute on the EMEA growth strategies in the Enterprise market. In addition, the Sales Manager will ensure the consistent alignment of sales, marketing, pre-sales, channels, delivery and operations to drive a cohesive and effective business. The position reports to the Sales Director Enterprise, France. The Sales Manager will lead a diverse team of employees, providing Go-to-Market coverage for France and is responsible Product Sales Achievement plus Services.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>&lt;u>&amp;nbsp;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/u>&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Establishing the strategy, direction and tone for managing part of the Enterprise vertical.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Developing and ensuring sales objectives are aligned with Juniper’s business strategy – through active participation in corporate strategic planning, sales strategy development, forecasting, sales resource planning and budgeting.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Meeting/Exceeding assigned targets for profitable sales volume, market share and other key financial performance objectives.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Leveraging, orchestrating and rallying the resources across the company to bring the full potential of the company’s resources to bear on sales opportunities.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Applying both tactical and strategic go-to-market models aimed at growing the customer base both in the short and long terms to drive higher revenues, customer growth and customer satisfaction and retention.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Influencing, engaging and enabling appropriate partners in support of our go-to-market strategy.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Manage directly a broad team of high performing Sales Leaders and Account Managers and set the agenda for Customer Service Leads, Architects, Managers and Sales Engineers supporting her/his business.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Driving performance, team development and deep relationships with clients.&lt;/li>
