&lt;p>&lt;strong>Sr Territory Account Manager&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>This is a Territory Account Manager position responsible for Mist sales for the Southwest Region (includes Southern California, Arizona, &amp; Denver, CO).&lt;/strong>&amp;nbsp; In this role, you will drive the Mist business as a specialist supporting the Juniper Commercial sales team as the subject matter sales expert for Juniper's industry leading AI-Driven Enterprise portfolio.&amp;nbsp; This includes managing all Mist-related sales activity, channel strategy, go-to-market, etc. to grow the business in the region.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Primary Responsibilities:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Owning the development and delivery of enterprise business development strategy&amp;nbsp;positioning Juniper’s Vision, Strategy and Architecture.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Identifying key metrics for success in expanding enterprise business.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Achieve agreed sales targets and use Sales Force tools (SFDC) to accurately record and measure the success of the strategy against these targets.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Working constructively and collaboratively with all key stakeholders to support business development strategy.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>This role is a remote role.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Candidate Background:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>More than 10 years’ experience selling within the IT sector with proven sales achievement exceeding objectives&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience working with enterprise customers is critical.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Broad-based technological awareness in the networking industry, complemented by knowledge of data networking concepts.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Proven ability to engage and negotiate with senior decision makers.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Personal Characteristics:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>High energy level, dynamic personality and action oriented,&lt;/li>
