&lt;p>&lt;strong>Sales Operations Leader: Lead to Cash&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Role&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The Sales Operations Leader will have a unique opportunity to engineer the business processes of the support functions essential to sales force productivity. These include sales process optimization, sales tool implementation, and working in tandem with IT, Sales, and cross-functional teams to achieve sales goals. The leader is responsible for the overall roadmap and effectiveness of the sales support processes with special focus on Lead to Order management.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>This role will balance transformation responsibilities with operational&amp;nbsp;responsibilities, as well as furthering the Future of Selling vision by undertaking global strategic projects from small to large scale.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Reporting to the Director of Sales Operations at Juniper Networks, this leader works closely with internal and external stakeholders to ensure the appropriate objectives and architecture roadmap are achieved.&amp;nbsp;This leader translates strategic imperatives into actionable plans targeted at optimizing sales execution, increasing agility, and enabling sales processes and tools to serve as a strategic lever for growth.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>As a leader in Sales Operations, the ideal candidate must excel in business acumen, communication, judgement, and consensus building to drive the necessary alignment between technology teams, business processes and a wide range of functional organizations. The primary stakeholders are Sales, Marketing, System Engineering, IT, Finance, and Services; being comfortable working with stakeholders at all levels.&lt;/p>
