&lt;p>As a Marketing Automation Sr Specialist, you will play a crucial role in managing and optimizing our marketing automation platform, Eloqua, to support marketing initiatives through development and optimization of our marketing automation platform. You will collaborate closely with the marketing team to ensure the successful execution of campaigns, demand generation, and customer engagement.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Eloqua Configuration and Governance&lt;/strong>: Configure, maintain, and troubleshoot our Eloqua instance to ensure optimal performance and functionality.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Campaign Management Escalation&lt;/strong>: Create, deploy, and monitor marketing campaigns, including email marketing, lead nurturing, and segmentation.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Database Management&lt;/strong>: Manage and maintain the Eloqua contact database, ensuring data cleanliness and compliance with data protection regulations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Automation Workflows&lt;/strong>: Maintain, govern, and develop automated workflows, including lead nurturing, lead scoring, lead flow and email marketing automation.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Analysis and Reporting&lt;/strong>: Generate reports and audit campaign performance to provide insights and provide recommendations for continuous improvement.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Integration&lt;/strong>: Collaborate with teams across Juniper, primarily our Marketing Innovation Center, to integrate Eloqua with other marketing systems ensuring data flow and synchronization.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Training and Documentation&lt;/strong>: Provide training and support to marketing teams on Eloqua best practices and maintain documentation for internal processes.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Compliance&lt;/strong>: Ensure compliance with data protection regulations, email marketing laws, and best practices.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Competencies &amp; Qualifications&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Business, or a related field.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Minimum of 3 years of experience as an Eloqua Administrator or in a similar marketing automation role.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Proficiency in Oracle Eloqua and its various modules.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Strong understanding of email marketing best practices.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience with lead scoring, segmentation, and automation workflows.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Familiarity with CRM systems (e.g., Salesforce) is a plus.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Strong communication and collaboration skills.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Ability to work independently and manage multiple tasks simultaneously.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Eloqua certification is a plus&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
