&lt;p>&lt;b>Job Description&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;b>Paid Media Operations Specialist&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Juniper Networks is seeking a motivated and talented Paid Media Operations Specialist to join our Paid Media Team and work alongside other internal marketing teams and external agencies to launch and monitor Paid Media programs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In this role you will be responsible for back-end set up and tracking for campaigns and creatives, ensuring data quality in our marketing dashboards, and lead management. Experience with Google DCM, LinkedIn Campaign Manager, and Eloqua is important.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;b>Key Accountabilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Campaign set-up and execution, including generating UTM parameters for tracking URLs, and testing ad tags for campaign launches&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Manage lead gen integration implementation, perform QA checks, and work with agency to launch form&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work with agency and web development team to implement tracking pixels when necessary&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Implement Juniper’s template and lead mapping process across Content Syndication programs&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Collecting and confirming content syndication list uploads into Eloqua&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Support Paid Media Managers by monitoring all reporting dashboards (Adobe Analytics, Tableau, Adverity), flagging any and all inconsistencies and owning the troubleshooting process&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Ensure ad creative adheres to technical specifications and troubleshoot creative issues that affect implementation, tracking and/or reporting&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Effectively communicate with agency/vendors to ensure the proper set-up and deployment of campaigns&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Maintain records of creative assets and internal documents that track proposals and campaign execution&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Provide recommendations and solutions to quickly resolve technical issues&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Additional projects and tasks supporting the Paid Media team as needed&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;b>Job Requirements&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>&lt;b>5 years of experience in digital marketing/advertising experience&lt;/b>&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>&lt;b>Minimum of 3 years’ experience in digital ad operations, media and site tagging, marketing analytics, digital campaign performance measurement with web analytics tools&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b>&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Proficient in trafficking ads across all platforms including assigning tracking codes, working with tracking requirements.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Able to dig deep into different stages of B2B funnel to understand KPIs and associated issues&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Excellent communication skills, strong collaboration, time management, project management, work in a fast-paced environment, strong eye for detail&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Hands-on experience with Eloqua, LinkedIn Campaign Manager, Salesforce&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Analytical mindset with the ability to derive insights from data&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Passionate, assertive and intellectually curious person looking to proactively identify problems and solving using data-driven approach&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
