&lt;p>Juniper Networks aspires to Connect Everything and Empower Everyone while helping our customers build the best networks on the planet through a remarkable customer experience.&amp;nbsp; In Component Engineering, Technology, and Quality (CETQ), our vision is to empower bulletproof networks by driving Juniper’s component quality to excellence and delivering reliable component technologies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>About the Position:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In this position within the CETQ department, you will work with engineers in the Packaging, Reliability, and Simulation group in utilizing finite element simulation to enable and accelerate the development of new components for Juniper Networks’ newest products.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>You will collaborate with other teams from multiple functional groups, to develop models and provide guidance for component design and reliability, which include semiconductor devices as well as other product families.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>You will have the opportunities to analyze and optimize the performance of state-of-the-art component technologies and system designs and make significant impact on improving quality and reliability for our products.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>You will also collaborate with hardware and mechanical design teams, to develop analysis workflows and simulation capabilities for system design-related thermo-mechanical and multi-physics simulations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Main Responsibilities include:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Use numerical simulation to conduct numerical experiments and modeling assessments on a variety of semiconductor devices reliability aspects including solder joint fatigue, warpage, and stress-strain evaluation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work with reliability engineers and collaborate with other teams inside Juniper on the understanding of hardware and system design, product development methods, and manufacturing processes. Assist in the evaluation of new and existing packages designs and provide insight on the effects of design variation on component- and system-level reliability.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Minimum Qualification:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Be pursuing a master’s degree with thesis option or a Ph.D. degree (preferred) in material science or mechanical engineering, or similar fields&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>A minimum 1-2 years of experience in the area of numerical simulation. Direct experience with ANSYS is a must.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Candidates who have published research work as authors or co-authored research articles, journal papers or conference papers, that show in their published work, the understanding of structure-property relationships and demonstrate the developing of solutions based on that understanding will be given priority for this internship.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Expertise in organic and inorganized materials properties, testing and characterization methods, and constitutive models. Familiarity with basic material failure modes: Fatigue, creep, and fracture mechanics is a must.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Must have excellent communication skills, both verbal and written.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Strong Excel, Power point, data visualization skills are required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Flexible on working hours, can accommodate global time zones.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>In addition, you will join our comprehensive University Talent Program that fosters personal as well as professional growth, thoroughly preparing interns for the next step in their careers. &amp;nbsp;Juniper internships are project-based, allowing interns to solve important problems, make lasting impacts on their teams, and contribute to the company’s overall objectives. &amp;nbsp;Interns are mentored by some of the most talented and skillful innovators in the industry; you will connect with transformative thought leaders who promote disruptive ideas in their field. You will also participate in constructive professional workshops, company-wide community service initiatives, and an executive speaker series.&amp;nbsp;You’ll build lasting friendships, expand your network, and connect with colleagues from around the world.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>At Juniper Networks, you will not only have opportunities to build real-life, hands-on work experience – you’ll also have the chance to&amp;nbsp;learn from the best&amp;nbsp;and lay the groundwork for a successful career.&lt;/p>
