&lt;p>&lt;strong>Global Commodity Manager – FPGAs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Location:&amp;nbsp; Bangalore, IN&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Juniper’s Supply Chain is a world class team with more than 400 members located globally. Our diverse, innovative, and highly adaptable team incorporates cutting-edge technologies to address the market’s changing needs. Through our development and fulfillment activities, Supply Chain strives to delight our customers in Enterprise, Cloud and Service Provider segments with the best network experience.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>About the Position:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The Commodity Manager will be responsible for the sourcing and commodity management of FPGAs and other semiconductors, from product concept to end of life. This critical individual will understand all market aspects and be recognized as a semiconductor industry expert.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Responsibilities:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Lead sourcing of all new FPGA components and manage the RFQ process and supplier selection&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Manage supplier relationships, negotiate contracts, and measure performance with regular business reviews&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Identify technology requirements for Juniper’s FPGA product roadmap.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Collaborate with cross-functional stakeholders, Distinguished Engineers and PLM to lead teams to develop, ratify, communicate and execute on a Global Technology and Business Strategy.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Be Juniper’s Supplier Base Technology and Business expert. Drive analytics for supply chain operations, develop business decision models for supply chain risks, develop execution plans and execute to reduce risks.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Build relationship with Suppliers’ Executives and negotiate silicon sourcing, IP acquisition, and NREs.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Represent Juniper’s needs to the industry and drive strategic partnerships to enable aligned investments and go-to-market strategies.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Identify value engineering opportunities and drive implementation with a cross functional team.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Drive Productivity Gains, Cost Reduction, Quality, Supplier Management and Business Review Programs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Create cost models and understand cost drivers.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work with technology partners, and in accordance with the commodity strategy, drive supplier selection, development and overall supplier management.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work with Engineering Leaders and Supplier Quality Engineering to integrate supplier performance requirements into all suppliers.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Develop commodity specific performance criteria and award/remove business in accordance with results.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work as key contributor on special projects and initiatives as needed&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
