&lt;p>&lt;strong>Role: Professional Services Consultant – Data Center &amp; IP Fabric SDN&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Location: Bangalore&lt;/strong>&lt;br/>&lt;br/>&lt;strong>About the Position:&lt;/strong>&lt;br/>&lt;br/>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>This highly technical role provides Architectural, Design, and Implementation Consultancy services for Junipers Networks Solutions targeted at Service Provider customers. The consultant must develop and maintain Data Center architecture &amp; solutions expertise and apply network automation through Fabric SDN controllers such as Juniper Apstra to ease their implementations and operations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>This role is a full-time post-sales position on-site and remote, working as part of a wider Juniper Professional Services team. This role will require 10% travel.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>What is Juniper Apstra?&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Apstra is Juniper’s newest acquisition, bringing state-of-the-art Data Center automation to its customers. It provides integrated design, deployment, and management of VXLAN / EVPN Clos fabric networks in a vendor-agnostic way through a single pane of glass. Using advanced automation technology, manual, bespoke design, and operational tasks have become a thing of the past.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;br/>&lt;strong>Responsibilities:&lt;/strong>&lt;br/>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>This position will be an Individual Contributor Role&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Run requirements and scoping workshops with customers, delivery partners, and sales.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Acting as a Technical lead for significant network deployments and migrations where responsibilities include delivery of Professional Services milestones, including creating high-level and low-level design documentation, migration planning, product integration, and acceptance.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Follow the Juniper Professional Services engagement and delivery processes, working closely with the Project Manager.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work closely with colleagues and customer personnel to help test, design, and plan for deployments of new products and features.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Support networks in the early stages of deployment&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Formulate network management strategies&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Act as a Professional Services project leader on larger projects, coordinating the work of a larger delivery team&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;owning overall responsibility for network implementation.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Provide appropriate training (Knowledge Transfer workshops) to Juniper Networks partners and customers.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Develop and maintain strong relationships with the customer's technical management and teams.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Participation in requirements gathering workshops, discussions, and meetings with Customer’s Design, Test, and/or Engineering Teams&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Providing input related to ‘best practices in design, implementation, and/or migration planning, and validation &amp; verification testing&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Assisting with hand-over to Operations or to a Juniper Networks Operational RE&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Tracking and reporting of issues found during testing, Implementation and migration&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Must Have Skills&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Expert communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Effective consultancy, planning &amp; communication skills, excellent interpersonal skills, ability to work on multiple projects and manage customers appropriately.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The mature “customer first” focus&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Strong planning and designing experience.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Commitment to delivering a remarkable customer experience.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Excellent and deep hands-on and planning capabilities in advanced Data Center technologies – VxLAN, EVPN, MCLAG, IP Fabric&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Strong knowledge of IP-related protocols, including IS-IS, OSPF, BGP, RSVP, LDP, QOS solutions, and IPv6 standards/protocols&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Familiar with any DC fabric SDN/manager/orchestration tool&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Hands-on experience with Linux servers and network services (DHCP, SNMP, FTP, TFTP, DNS, NTP).&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Basic knowledge of data structures, algorithms, HTTP/REST APIs&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Familiar with Linux, Python, and version control systems such as Git&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Fluent in English and Spanish and have excellent written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong>Desirable Education and Experience:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Bachelor or Master of Science in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a similar discipline&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>5+ years’ experience in the enterprise/telco/content provider Data Center environment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong>Desirable Skills:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>JUNOS skills and hands-on planning capabilities with QFX, EX, and MX Series products.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
