&lt;p>&lt;strong>ABOUT JUNIPER NETWORKS&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Juniper Networks is in the business of network innovation. From devices to data centers, from consumers to cloud providers, Juniper Networks delivers the software, silicon and systems that transform the experience and economics of networking. Our products and technology run the world's largest and most demanding networks today, enabling service providers, enterprises, and governments to create value and accelerate business success. Everyday our 9,000+ colleagues come together across 46 countries to realize our company vision - Connect Everything, Empower Everyone. We are innovating in ways that empower our customers, our partners and ultimately, everyone, in a connected world. These customers include the top 130 global service providers, 96 of the Fortune 100 and hundreds of public sector organizations.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>WHERE WILL YOU DO YOUR BEST WORK?&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Wherever you are in the world, whether it's downtown Sunnyvale or London, Westford or Bangalore, Juniper is a place that was founded on disruptive thinking - where colleague innovation is not only valued but expected. We believe that the great task of delivering a new network for the next decade is delivered through the creativity and commitment of our people. The Juniper Way is the commitment to all our colleagues that the culture and company inspire their best work-their life's work. At Juniper we believe this is more than a job - it's an opportunity to help change the world.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Role: Professional Services Consultant (Security)&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Location: Bangalore&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The Juniper Networks Professional Services Security Consultant is a knowledgeable trusted advisor to our customers. In this role, the candidate will be required to&amp;nbsp;analysis, design and implementation of Juniper Networks solutions. Excellent communication and technical skills will be required to develop and maintain customer relationship and to exceed customers’ expectations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Key Responsibilities:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>The Professional Services Consultant will act as a Trusted Advisor to customers and assist with all phases of network development from planning to operation and optimization.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The Professional Services Consultant will be a subject matter expert for implementing Juniper Networks products and solutions with strong emphasis on the Juniper Security Portfolio including Branch SRX, High-End SRX, Security Director, Juniper Secure Analytics (JSA), SKY ATP and Policy Enforcer.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The Professional Services Consultant will provide input related to ‘best practices’ in design, implementation and/or migration planning.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The Professional Services Consultant will be expected to create High Level Design, Low Level Design, Test Plans, Implementation and Migration plans.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The Professional Services Consultant will educate customers on new Juniper software and hardware features.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The Professional Services Consultant will be expected to provide customers with technical information and documentation related to Juniper Networks products.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The Professional Services Consultant will participate in requirements gathering workshops, discussions and meetings with Customer’s Design, Test and/or Engineering Teams.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The Professional Services Consultant will evaluate customer networks for performance, scalability, and security and provide recommendations to customers about improvements to network configurations and topologies to prevent problems before they occur.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The Professional Services Consultant will be constantly expanding their realm of product experience.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>The Professional Services Consultant will be expected to manage their own schedule andbe able to work independently to satisfy multiple customer projects concurrently.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Work in a consultative manner to support&amp;nbsp; enterprise wireless solutions.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Designing, planning and implementing solutions using the MIST Wireless&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Develop and maintain an in-depth technical knowledge of the MIST wireless product lines.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Skills and Experience:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>Expert communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Self-starter with a passion for Technology&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Commitment to delivering a remarkable customer experience&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Ability to work independently and manage multiple projects as required&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Demonstrated experience as collaborative team-player&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Industry Certifications – Juniper product certifications (JNCIA/JNCIS/JNCIP) preferred but not required&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience/Knowledge of IP networks&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Understanding of basic Network Security Principles&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Knowledge of Juniper JunOS and Juniper Products&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Ability to execute projects using scripting and/or relevant programming languages, for example, shell, Python, Ansible, Ruby, PERL, SLAX, JavaScript, XML&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience/Knowledge of Linux/Unix based systems&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Hands-on configuration and operational knowledge of Juniper Networks SRX firewalls and/or of the following security products: Cisco, Check Point, Juniper Networks/Netscreen ScreenOS Firewalls, ISS, Tipping Point, Remote Access solutions, QRadar, Juniper Secure Analytics (JSA), Junos Space, Junos Security Director&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience with VPNs and the associated tunneling technologies and architectures (IPSEC, GRE, hub and spoke)&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience with NAT (Source, Destination, Static, CGN, NAT-PT)&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Knowledge of virtualization technologies&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience with Juniper, Cisco or other major vendor Ethernet switches&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience with Juniper, Cisco or other major vendor&amp;nbsp;routers&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience/Knowledge in dynamic routing protocols (OSPF, BGP)&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Strong skills and excellent hands-on and planning capabilities with,
  &lt;ul>
   &lt;li>Juniper CSO,SRX,&amp;nbsp; SSR(128T) or other SDWAN Products like Versa, Cisco Viptela, Silver peak.&lt;/li>
   &lt;li>Mist AP and Cloud or Similar cloud based wireless solution from other vendors like Aruba, Extreme Networks, Cisco Meraki.&lt;/li>
  &lt;/ul>&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Familiar with Wireless technologies&amp;nbsp; like IEEE 802.11 standards (b,g,n, ac,ax), 802.1x Wi-Fi&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Good knowledge of&amp;nbsp;Controller based or cloud based wireless management and solutions.&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>Experience designing, deploying, configuring, supporting, troubleshooting, debugging and administering some of the following Wireless LAN products, devices, and technologies for small, medium, large and/or enterprise businesses such as the following:&lt;br/>* Wireless Access Points&lt;br/>* Wireless Client Association&lt;br/>* Wireless Controllers&lt;br/>* CSMA/CA, RTS, CTS protocols&lt;br/>* RF transmission/site survey&lt;br/>* Antennas&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>* WEP encryption (Wired Equivalent Privacy) , WPA (Wi-Fi Protocol Access), WPA2&lt;/p>
