&lt;p>Product Knowledge: &amp;nbsp;EX, QFX&lt;br/> &lt;strong>Clearance Requirement: &amp;nbsp;Public Trust&lt;/strong>&lt;br/> Location: &amp;nbsp;Remote&lt;br/> Travel: &amp;nbsp;Minimal travel can be expected&lt;/p> 
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Who We Are&lt;/strong>&lt;/p> 
&lt;p>Juniper Networks, Inc. is the leader in high-performance networking. We offer ample growth, training, and leadership opportunities for candidates with a passion for Networking and the Internet. &amp;nbsp;We are constantly seeking talented technical professionals with all levels of networking and network security skills who are interested in a career working with customers both nationally and internationally. Our employees are in a unique position to expand their interests, realize their full potential, and build a reputation with a recognized industry leader.&lt;/p> 
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Job Description &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>&lt;/p> 
&lt;p>This position will be primarily remote, with on-site support at the customer locations as requested. &amp;nbsp;Support to the customer will require the RE to have:&lt;/p> 
&lt;ul> 
 &lt;li>Minimum 7 - 10 years of hands-on network engineering experience&lt;/li> 
 &lt;li>Strong network engineering background with a primary focus on layer 2 switch administration&lt;/li> 
 &lt;li>Strong experience with EVPN/VXLAN and BGP&lt;/li> 
 &lt;li>Knowledge of and experience working with IPV6 a plus&lt;/li> 
 &lt;li>Products to support: EX &amp; QFX, Mist Wireless and SDWAN (Optional)&lt;br/> &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li> 
&lt;/ul> 
&lt;p>Ideal Strengths and Experiences&lt;/p> 
&lt;ul> 
 &lt;li>Expert level relationship management, communications skills, and interpersonal skills to manage face-to-face communications daily with multiple levels of customer management and engineering staff across multiple departments within the host company in a responsible and professional fashion&lt;/li> 
 &lt;li>Customer culture is strong technical team with deep expertise across multiple layers of technical responsibility&lt;/li> 
 &lt;li>Expert-level troubleshooting methodology to isolate and identify configuration, design, and software anomalies; ability to clearly articulate findings in written and verbal communications with development-level engineering staff&lt;/li> 
 &lt;li>Ability to apply knowledge to real-world scenarios&lt;/li> 
 &lt;li>Demonstrated ability to manage multiple projects and work calmly under pressure&lt;/li> 
 &lt;li>Self-starter, team player, personable, enthusiastic, hardworking, and enjoy interfacing with customers on a day-to-day basis.&lt;/li> 
 &lt;li>A plus to have hands-on configuration and operational knowledge of other vendor products and their operation&lt;/li> 
 &lt;li>The ability to see a need and insert/suggest Juniper technology or reach out to the sales team and suggest same&lt;/li> 
&lt;/ul> 
